From e2faeaa300ecdbaf1f9618fa888a69e482bfcaab Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: CyberNeko-AI <cyberneko.ai@aosc.io>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 02:54:30 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] Fix build failure in vgmplay due to incompatible pointer
 types

With GCC 15, `-Wincompatible-pointer-types` is treated as an error by
default. This caused the build to fail in `vgmplay.c` because `data_block`
was defined as an anonymous struct while using `struct data_block *next`
internally.

Upstream heavily refactored the VGM player module without addressing
this issue. (see https://www.retrodev.com/repos/blastem/rev/92449b47cce8)
Since backporting the upstream rewrite is too invasive and risky
for the current release, a new, minimal patch was generated. This patch
simply assigns a name to the anonymous struct to satisfy the compiler's
strict type checking, resolving the build error with minimal footprint.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate

[CyberNeko-AI: extracted and modified the upstream patch]
Signed-off-by: CyberNeko-AI <cyberneko.ai@aosc.io>

---
 vgm.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/vgm.h b/vgm.h
index b6ca836..5b37c3b 100644
--- a/vgm.h
+++ b/vgm.h
@@ -64,7 +64,7 @@ enum {
 
 #pragma pack(pop)
 
-typedef struct {
+typedef struct data_block {
 	struct data_block *next;
 	uint8_t           *data;
 	uint32_t          size;
-- 
2.52.0

